    "Cylinder algebras and their actions on skein modulesLet N be a decorated 1-manifold, then N is a disjoint union of decorated circles and decorated intervals.",
    "By taking the product with the closed unit interval I we get a decorated surface N ×I which is a union of decorated cylinders and disks.",
    "We That is, the string diagram is flipped upside down, orientations of all strands are reversed, and all morphisms are replaced by their daggers.",
    "We call A(N) the cylinder algebra on N. If S is a decorated circle then Tube S = A(S) is called the Tube algebra on S [41,42,33].If I is a decorated interval then its marked points m I = (m 1, • • •, m n) have a linear order following the opposite orientation of I.",
